= Preface

This starter book is for absolute beginners. It does not try to cover every rule of Dutch. Instead, it gives you the grammar you will meet early and often: articles, pronouns, word order, present tense verbs, negation, and common question patterns.

The best way to use it is slowly:

- Read one short section at a time.
- Say the Dutch examples out loud.
- Copy a few patterns and replace one word with your own word.
- Revisit word order often. In Dutch, word order is one of the biggest early wins.

You do not need to memorize everything on the first pass. If you can already understand how a sentence is built, you are making progress.
